1. Windows
Strengths: 
Easy to use and widely available
Compatible with most software and games

Weaknesses:
Prone to viruses
Paid license

Best For:
Students, office work, and gaming.

2. Mac (macOS)
Strengths:
Smooth performance and great design
Strong security and good for creative work

Weaknesses:
Expensive hardware
Limited to Apple devices

Best For:
Graphic design, video editing, and Apple users.

3. Linux
Strengths:
Free and open-source
Very secure and customizable

Weaknesses:
Not beginner-friendly
Some software may not work

Best For:
Developers, servers, and tech-savvy users.
